      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NANGAR POLLY (2) was strongly fancied and drifted back but wound up hard to hit the frame, 3 lengths from the winner (30.03) at this track in Grade 5. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Overdue and is among the main hopes. ZIPPING KAYLI (7) settled just off the lead last start then drew clear late to score her maiden win over 520m at this track (29.59). Will break from a wide draw. Leading player again. WOOLGOOLGA (8) turned in a good run last time, finishing in the placings (29.94) at this track in a Grade 5. Lines up from box 8 for the first time. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Expecting another good run. EXTREME MACHINE (3) can measure up with the right run.",
